===Etymology===
From {{L.}} '''[[metaphysica]]''' < Byzantine Greek '''{{polytonic|[[μεταφυσικά]]}}''' (metaphusika) < {{AGr.}}  '''{{polytonic|[[μετά]]}}''' (meta) "after" + '''{{polytonic|[[φυσικός]]}}''' (phusikos) "natural".  The word derives from the title of the collection by Aristotle "μετὰ τὰ φυσικά" (after the natural things).

